# Cursor IDE Optimization Rules for Go Project

## Performance Optimizations

- Limit file indexing to essential directories
- Exclude large binary files and build artifacts
- Optimize Go language server settings

## File Exclusions

- Exclude vendor/ directories from indexing
- Exclude .git/ directory from deep scanning
- Exclude build artifacts and temporary files
- Exclude node_modules if any exist

## Go-specific Settings

- Enable Go modules support
- Use minimal language server features to reduce CPU usage
- Disable unnecessary Go diagnostics for better performance

## Memory Management

- Limit number of concurrent file operations
- Reduce syntax highlighting complexity for large files
- Optimize intellisense caching

## Indexing Preferences

- Focus on .go files primarily
- Limit deep directory traversal
- Exclude test files from heavy analysis when not needed
